area type manager allows area types to be defined
e.g.: overworld, underground, etc

instead of numbers for skins and backgrounds, a json file allows easy identification

e.g.:
assets/areatypes/overworld.json
{
    "background:" #6084F8
    "music": ".../.../file.mp3"
}

thus ->
assets/models/brick.json
{
  "textures": [
    {"overworld": "tiles/brick.png"},
    {"underground": "tiles/brick_ug.png"}
  ]
}

level file will also allow overriding of music